*   [No. 256 Squadron RAF](/No._256_Squadron_RAF): Maintained a detachment at Middle Wallop between 6 February and 26 March 1941, flying the Defiant I. [21]
*   [No. 286 Squadron RAF](/No._286_Squadron_RAF): Operated as a detachment at Middle Wallop sometime between April 1942 and 1944, utilizing a range of aircraft including the Master III, Defiant I & III, Hurricane I & IIX, and the Oxford. [22]
*   [No. 400 Squadron RCAF](/400_Tactical_Helicopter_Squadron): Stationed at the airfield between 4 December 1942 and 1 February 1943, flying the Mustang I. [23]
*   [No. 406 Squadron RCAF](/406_Maritime_Operational_Training_Squadron): Served at Middle Wallop from 8 December 1942 to 31 March 1943, operating the Beaufighter VIF. [23]
